cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.PL. 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper aims to encourage the software engineering community to use formal verification tools. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper introduces the language and verifier Dafny. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper discusses Hoare-style verification. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses automated verification tools. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is mentioned again as the paper discusses using Dafny as an assistant in the development of verified programs.
